node.text: Collaborated with @Qualcomm for this Mobile Photography Tutorial! Shot on the #Snapdragon 888 5G Mobile Platform! Check out @SnapdragonInsiders for more pro-quality #ShotOnSnapdragon photos [ad]

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Washington. May be an image of nature, road and tree.

node.text: Big mountains here out west 🏔 it was awesome this particular one blow up in a crazy morning glow on its glaciers

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Washington with @kierra_summer. May be an image of nature.

node.text: A perfect evening in the mountains. Summertime here as been flawless so far 😌 Stoked for more camping + hiking these next couple months

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Hawaii. May be an image of nature, ocean and sky.

node.text:
This was one of those photos I was unsure of editing. You be the judge. 

Shot this recently on my trip to Hawaii. It was the perfect example as to why you need to give some places a second chance

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Hawaii with @jessicabertken. May be an image of nature, beach, sky and ocean.

node.text: Island vibes comin’ in hot 🏝 We spent all morning hanging out at this beach getting our tan on. I’d say it’s a pretty solid way to start the day if I do say so myself 🤠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Argentina with @ryanresatka. May be an image of mountain and nature.

node.text: Some of the craziest places out there are waiting for you to discover them. Get out and make your dreams happen 🌎

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Hawaii. May be an image of ocean and nature.

node.text: One of the most absolutely stunning coast lines ever. This definitely changed my perception about traveling to more tropical places in the future. The earth is so beautiful and every bit deserves attention 😌🌏

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in California with @willowfantino. May be an image of mountain, twilight, sky and nature.

node.text: Sometimes unplanned summer hikes can lead to the best views. You never know what you’ll get. This hike was very special because these were some of my favorite photos I captured that was near where I lived at the time. It’s about finding opportunity

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Hawaii. May be an image of nature and ocean.

node.text: You gotta love those Hawaiian beach views 🏝 The crazy mountains make this place absolutely next level. I’m definitely going to be visiting more tropical places in the near future 😎 I feel like it’s a huge component that’s been missing from my travels and it’s a huge part of seeing everything. I’d love to hear suggestions if y’all have any. Definitely have SE Asia + Indo on the list.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Lake Tahoe. May be an image of nature, lake and ocean.

node.text: Summer Tahoe vibes 💧 I could only imagine how awesome it would be boating around on a hot summer day drifting above this lake’s insanely clear water

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Hawaii with @jessicabertken. May be an image of nature.

node.text: Crazy ridges. Just got back from a trip to Hawaii and it was beyond awesome! Such an amazing mix of nature, hiking, and relaxation. I will say though the hikes are no joke. Most of them are deemed “Hike at your own risk”. I definitely want you guys to know that because there are some places out here, whether it’s near the ocean or high up on a ridge, where it can definitely be a little sketchy. With that said as long as you’re willing to go a little out of your comfort zone and you’re extra careful you can definitely be rewarded with some of the best views of your life. I can’t wait to plan my next trip there 😌🏝

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Japan. May be an image of nature.

node.text: Here’s a photo from a perfect afternoon with Mount Fuji in full view. I had spent the day exploring this village and the lake nearby, taking in the sights, food, and occasionally people watching 😂

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Washington with @tyehaus. May be an image of nature.

node.text: A perfect place to stay for the night 🏠 The warm glow of the Foss Haus, part of the @tyehaus family of cabins is quite inviting. The photo sums up a near-perfect evening with friends. Also - I shot this on my new camera. The dynamic range and lowlight capabilities are absolutely nuts. I don’t think this image would’ve been possible on my one camera
